    "q": "What is the best time of day to write in a gratitude journal?",
    "a": "The best time is whenever you can be consistent. Many people prefer the morning to set a positive tone for the day, or the evening to reflect and promote better sleep."
  },
  {
    "q": "How can I avoid gratitude fatigue?",
    "a": "To avoid gratitude fatigue, try to be specific instead of repeating the same broad things. Focus on small, detailed moments, and vary your categories (e.g., people, nature, self)."
  },
  {
    "q": "Do I need a special notebook for a gratitude journal?",
    "a": "No, any notebook or piece of paper works. You can also use digital apps, a bullet journal, or even a gratitude jar. The medium matters less than the practice itself."
  },
  {
    "q": "Can gratitude journaling help with anxiety?",
    "a": "Yes, research shows that regularly practicing gratitude can shift your focus away from toxic emotions and negative spirals, helping to lower stress and reduce symptoms of anxiety."
  },
  {
    "q": "What is the 'Three Good Things' exercise?",
    "a": "The 'Three Good Things' exercise involves writing down three positive things that happened each day and reflecting on why they happened. It's a simple, evidence-based way to boost happiness."
  }
];

